   "source": [
    "# Make your own surface data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "CTSM needs lots of surface variables to run. \n",
    "\n",
    "CTSM technical notes has the official tutorial for creating surface datasets.\n",
    "\n",
    "[**CTSM technical notes 1.3.5 Creating Surface data**](https://escomp.github.io/ctsm-docs/versions/release-clm5.0/html/users_guide/using-clm-tools/creating-surface-datasets.html)\n",
    "\n",
    "However, it is difficult to use the tool for users that are not familiar to CESM/CTSM. Because in pyclmuapp, we mainly focus on urban climate and the percentage of urban is set to 100%, which means the output are only urban related. Hence, we can easily over-write the urban surface data in the default `surfdata.nc` provided by pyclmuapp, this avoids the complex steps of using the mksurfdata_map tools."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "**How to get our own urban surface data of the interest point from CESM provided file**\n",
    "\n",
    "Ref: [Technical Description of an Urban Parameterization for the Community Land Model (CLMU)](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/261062625_Technical_Description_of_an_Urban_Parameterization_for_the_Community_Land_Model_CLMU),\n",
    "    [Table 3 Input data required for the urban model](https://www.researchgate.net/figure/3-Input-data-required-for-the-urban-model_tbl1_261062625)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Workflow:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. get the urban surface input from [`mksrf_urban_0.05x0.05_simyr2000.c120621.nc`](https://svn-ccsm-inputdata.cgd.ucar.edu/trunk/inputdata/lnd/clm2/rawdata/)\n",
    "2. get the soil parameter for the pervious road in urban from [`mksrf_soitex.10level.c010119.nc`](https://svn-ccsm-inputdata.cgd.ucar.edu/trunk/inputdata/lnd/clm2/rawdata/)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pyclmuapp import usp_clmu\n",
    "from pyclmuapp import get_urban_params\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "import xarray as xr\n",
    "import os"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

   "source": [
